  prohibited by a cooling‑off period from taking up the intended
  occupational activity and, as a result, are unemployed; entitlement
  is subject to the conditions laid down in the Staff Rules (ECB
  Conditions of Employment, page 18).  - Monthly unemployment
  allowance: 60% of last basic salary for six months; then 30% of last
  basic salary for the subsequent six months and additional months in
  relation to years of service and age (ECB Conditions of Employment,
  page 17).   - Household and child allowances (ECB Conditions of
  Employment, page 17).   - Continued cover under the ECB health
  insurance, long‑term care insurance and accident insurance scheme,
  subject to payment of the relevant contributions (ECB Conditions of
  Employment, page 17).   - Education allowance (reimbursement): up to
  EUR 393 per month, except for children with certified, imperative
  educational needs when the reimbursement is increased to a maximum
  of EUR 764; the allowance is payable only until the end of the
  academic year in which the member of staff becomes unemployed and
  provided that the child remains (ECB Conditions of Employment, page
  17).   - One‑off severance‑type payment: one month’s salary at Band
  A, step 1 payable for each full year of service completed upon
  evidence of registration as unemployed and seeking employment; this
  payment shall in no case be lower than the equivalent of three
  months’ salary at Band A, step 1 and shall in no case exceed the
  equivalent of twelve months’ salary at Band A, step 1 (ECB
  Conditions of Employment, page 18).   - If the contract is
  terminated during the probationary period, a one‑off payment of an
  additional monthly basic salary (ECB Conditions of Employment, page
  18).   - Any benefits of the same nature provided by other sources
  must be claimed and declared and will be deducted from amounts
  payable under these provisions (ECB Conditions of Employment, page
