  consulting and her gross annual pension. These amounts are to be
  taken for the calendar year preceding the year in respect of which
  eligibility is assessed and must be measured before tax and before
  deduction of social security contributions. (ECB Staff Rules, page
  63, 3.5.1).   - Do not include investment income or capital gains in
  that total. (ECB Staff Rules, page 63, 3.5.1).   - Compare the
  resulting total to the threshold of EUR 71,764: the household
  allowance is payable only if your spouse’s gross annual income does
  not exceed EUR 71,764. (ECB Conditions of Employment, page 9).   -
  Provide evidence of the income (for example, the latest tax
  declaration and salary statement or other documents the ECB
  considers acceptable). (ECB Staff Rules, page 63, 3.5.2).   - If
  both you and your spouse are ECB staff, note that entitlements are
  assessed on a single‑household basis and, where both earn less than
